RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 11800. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 7 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 7 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 7 Allowed 4 l bs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPOOKY ONE led the way on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, pulled away in upper stretch and held of a closer at the wire. FEDERAL CASE raced off the pace on the outside early, navigated the turn from the two path and gained ground steadily late. ACT OF VALOR pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the bend and weakened in the final furlong. MISCHIEVOUS JONES trailed the field on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and and passed tiring horses in the stretch. AGAINST THE ODDS raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the early going, came around the turn in the three path and was empty in the lane. REFUND RIGLER stumbled leaving the gate, recovered to track the leaders up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and faded from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 10000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 7. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAKE NAKURU raced in the three path around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far bend and kicked clear in the lane. CARTE BLANCHE raced in the two path early, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the second turn, was caught entering the stretch and chased the winner home. POCOPSON STATION stalked the leaders on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn still in the three path and finished evenly. STAY HYDRATED raced in the two path around the first turn, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the three path and made no bid. HOT AND HEAVY saved ground early, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the three path around the far turn and was empty in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 90. Claiming Purse 19000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 7 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 7 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $9,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Ente red For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) Preference to horses with the most starts at Penn National since May 31st 2022. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlo ngs.) (Rail at 14 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLASHINTHENIGHT vied for the lead on the inside, checked hard and dropped back at the five sixteenths marker, shifted out and made a three wide bid and drew clear in the final furlong to prove best, driving. GRAB THE GOLD vied on the lead in between rivals through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and made a inside bid getting through by the furlong marker dug in gamely keeping on to the wire while being out-kicked by the winner. CARGO SHIP was hustled along under crop urging early four wide came around the bend in the four path and improved position in the stretch. MERU raced off the pace up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path and improved position mildly in the lane. HELLO'NDUBAI was bumped with the horse to his outside at the start, then vied for the lead three wide on the outside of a trio through the opening quarter, then made a two wide bid to draw clear by the quarter pole, but weakened in the final furlong. EDWARD MADDEN raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and faded in the stretch. CHEERS FOR KITTEN stumbled and bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, trailed the field up the backstretch, came around the turn in the two path and made no bid.

ENTRY.NAME: Flashinthenight
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, checked 5/16, shift 3 wide, bid 3 wide, drew clear,

ENTRY.NAME: Grab the Gold
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between horses, bid inside 1/8, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Hello'ndubai
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, vied 3 wide, bid 2 wide, clear, weakened 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Cargo Ship
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled 4 wide, chased 4 wide, no kick, bested rest

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 11800. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 7 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 7 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KEEPING IT COUNTRY chased the leader up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and kicked clear in the lane. ZOOMSTER raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, navigated the bend from the three path and chased the winner home to the wire. BUFF AND SHINE raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the four path, began a bid approaching the stretch and finished evenly. COUSIN BOB trailed the field on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, raced in the four path around the turn and passed tiring horses in the lane. I'LL FINISH raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and faded from there. ABHAR brushed lightly with the horses to either side leaving the gate, recovered to lead the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 57. Claiming Purse 10800. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 7 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HI HEELED WARRIOR raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far turn and kicked clear in the lane. LADYNESS saved ground, led the way up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend, was caught entering the stretch and kept on to the wire. BO RUNKLE saved ground early, tracked the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the second turn from the three path and finished evenly. SIMPLE JUSTICE raced in the two path around the first turn, settled off the pace on inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the second turn and was empty in the lane. ALL THE WAY MAE raced off the pace in the three path through through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the two path and made no bid.

ENTRY.NAME: All the Way Mae
ENTRY.OWNER: Deiter Kelly Lynn and T J Albert Racing LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 11800. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 7 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since July 7 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUCK WILD raced in the three path early, settled at the back of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the second turn and kicked clear. SYNONYM led the field from the two path through the opening half mile, continued around the second bend still in the two path, was caught near the quarter pole and chased on to the wire. MR BOLDACIOUS raced in the two path early, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, came around the second turn in the four path and gained ground mildly in the lane. MIDNIGHT STRIKES raced in the two path around the first bend, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and weakened in the stretch. LONG TOM raced in the three path at the back of the pack around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path and made no bid. LUCID saved ground early, chased the leader up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far turn and continued to tire in the stretch.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Lady Olivia at North Cliff Farm

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IF WE GET LUCKY led the way throughout, raced in the three path around the bend and drew off in the stretch. BULLET BREEZE raced off the pace on the outside early, came around the turn in the two path and improved position late. LETSGETLUCKYTONITE raced at the back of the pack on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued around the bend in the four path and passed tiring horses on the outside from there. BOB'S OUR UNCLE raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and weakened in the stretch. HIGHGATE chased the leader up the backstretch, continued pursuit of that rival from the three path around the bend and faded between horses in the lane. SYLVIA I AM raced at the back of the pack on the inside early, came around the turn in the three path and offered no bid. DISCREETLY THRIFTY raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and was empty in the stretch.
